.TH "img_ascii_lcd_display" 9 "img_ascii_lcd_display" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
img_ascii_lcd_display \- set the message to be displayed
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" img_ascii_lcd_display
.BI "(struct img_ascii_lcd_ctx *ctx "  ","
.BI "const char *msg "  ","
.BI "ssize_t count "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ctx" 12
pointer to the private data structure
.IP "msg" 12
the message to display
.IP "count" 12
length of msg, or -1
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Display a new message \fImsg\fP on the LCD. \fImsg\fP can be longer than the number of
characters the LCD can display, in which case it will begin scrolling across
the LCD display.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, -ENOMEM on memory allocation failure
